The hook should# exit with non-zero status after issuing an appropriate message if# it wants to stop the commit.## To enable this hook, rename this file to "pre-commit".if git rev-parse --verify HEAD >/dev/null 2>&1then        against=HEADelse        # Initial commit: diff against an empty tree object        against=4b825dc642cb6eb9a060e54bf8d69288fbee4904fi# If you want to allow non-ASCII filenames set this variable to true.allownonascii=$(git config --bool hooks.allownonascii)# Redirect output to stderr.exec 1>&2# Cross platform projects tend to avoid non-ASCII filenames; prevent# them from being added to the repository.
